        <num>38-4-54</num>
        <content>
          <p>All federal funds received by the Veterans Service Board and paid into the state treasury are continually appropriated to the Veterans Service Board in the exact amounts, for the care and support of disabled war veterans, as received from the federal government. This is not intended as a limitation upon the power of the General Assembly to make such additional appropriation to provide for the care and support of disabled veterans as it may from time to time see fit to make.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1955, Ex. Sess., p. 18, ยง 7; Ga. L. 1960, p. 1150, ยง 4.)</p>
